How many ways can you combine the side dishes?<n>Output: Choices A: 23 (2,3) B: 321 (4,8) C: 240 (3,3) D: 15!<n>Final answer C<n><n>Input:Several friends are considering going to a museum, a movie, or an art gallery on Saturdays. They will consider going to any of these locations, in any order. How many different ways are there to schedule the visits, assuming they can do each thing?<n>Output: Choice D<n><n>Input: A 2 person football team will consist of 1 quarterback and 1 running back/end.<n>The 3 person team (one quarterback is replaced with a receiver) will consist of 1 running back/ end, 1 quarterback and one receiver.<n>The four person team will consist of 2 running back/ends, 2 quarterbacks and 1 receiver.<n>The 5 person team will have 3 running back ends, 3 quarterbacks and 4 receivers.<n>Each team can be in 2 different combinations of each position (1 of every player 5 ways, 2 quarterback 2 ways, running back 2 ways).<n>The first case has 2 ways, 2nd case 3 ways, and the third case 4 ways.  In total the number of ways to combine any number of players is (n-1c) where n is the max and c is the number of times all players could be excluded.  So this adds up to (4-1)*2 = 5.<n>The total permutations of all combinations in all directions must also include the empty set since the person who would sit out will change every time but there must be the ability of a person not to play.  So the total permutations equal n choose 0 = 5.<n>Both factors (nchoose0 5) + (5 choose 1) = 5! The correct answer is (5 choose 0)
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Stanley had a dream that was very vivid and scary. He had trouble telling it from what? Choices:  A: reality B: imagination C: dreamworker D: nightmare E: awake<n>Output:		I know they asked for the letter ‘E ‘so maybe for E I will have to look into the definition to make sure that it can be correct.<n><n>E = a person who makes people realize their dreams and helps them to live a good life<n><n>So the answer is ‘A’<n><n>Input:What is an anonymizer? a b c d<n>Output: I choose to look up the word anonymizer to know what the correct answer should be.<n>https://www.google.com/search?oe=utf-8&q=anonymiz&gws_rd=cr|adw:krakatau&ei=vp2YUZ-xGML-vwPf_4HYCQ<n>It comes up with an option that anonymizer can be related to a proxy server.<n>A proxy server allows clients (generally individuals using their Internet browser) to avoid having their IP address revealed to websites they visit. Since all requests go through this gateway, websites see the address of the proxy server instead of the address of the client. Proxy servers are a kind of anonymizer, typically used to cloak a user's true IP address or geolocation so that websites will only be able to see a single IP address, that of the particular proxy.<n>And according to another site the definition and explanation of anonymizer is a software that allows someone to conceal their name (or IP address) when sending information over the internet. It is specifically used for internet browsing in order to prevent the websites you are browsing from knowing your identity and where you are logging on to the site<n>So the answer is option ‘B’ Anonymizer <n><n>Input:If the 13th, 27th, and 38th day of the month are Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday, what is the rest of the days of the month? a. Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Sally lost her kite because she wasn't careful. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Sometimes fighting inflation isn't even what, because it is so negligible? Choices:  A: economic instability B: not noticeable C: spend more D: rising interest rates E: boring<n>Output:		C<n><n>Input: You are going to need 50 apples to make apple pie.  You also need 120 bananas for the banana cream pie.   How many pies can you make?<n>Output: 50+120 =<<50+12=62>>62<n><n>Input: You're going to need 10 pumpkins for the pumpkin pies and 10 plums for the plum pies.   How many pias can you make?<n><n>Output: The choices to make pias are: the one with 10 and the one with 16<n><n>Input:I think the answer is 9<n>>>$5+$5+7+$5+$13+2+$5+$5<n>Output:I think the answer should be 19<n>>>$5-$6+$7-4<n><n>Input:You can only choose a number or blank option.<n>Input:You can choose any number from 1 to 100.<n>Output:The answers to choose with 1 are<n><n>>>2<n>>>5<n>>>7<n>>>11<n>And<n><n>>>25<n>>>26<n>>>34<n>>>42<n><n>Input:This is a 5 digit number.<n>Input:This is an 8 digit number, you have to add a zero to the front.<n>Output:The answer is:285264<n><n>Input:The cost of renting a movie is a multiple of 1 and a power of another number. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:What is necessary for learning by yourself? Choices:  A: exposure B: patience C: study D: cooperation E: thought<n>Output:		 You have to be willing to learn and be patient. You need to find other people that can teach you and show you how everything is done. You need to have study time. You need to be able to ask questions and think about what is going on.<n>So the final Answer for Learning by Yourself? is DACB<n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:What enables most people to transport themselves? Choices:  A: helicopter B: own cars C: speak words D: believe in god E: dance together<n>Output:		Answer Choice E was the best choice.<n>Answer:  E.<n><n>Input: What has four wheels, moves by itself, but when you try to go somewhere it makes you hot? Choices: A: Bus B: Taxi C: Car D: Train E: Bike<n>Output: Answer Choices A and B were valid choices, but answer choice E was the best answer (it makes you sweaty, and your sweat moves you farther from your destination).<n>Answer:  B.<n><n>Input: This is a test. Do the following to prove you have read and understood everything that was written here. Choices: A: Open my web browser B: Open a notepad.txt file C: Click on the link. D: Open a new folder and give it a name. B. C.<n>Output: Answer Choises A,B,C and D were valid choices, but this exam did not contain questions 2 through 4 thus Answer choice B was the best answer.<n>Answer:  C.<n><n>--- 
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where must one wear a white shoe? Choices:  A: wedding B: tennis C: closet D: left foot E: house<n>Output:		A: white shoes are worn at a wedding. <n>B: white shoes are not worn, as it is a sporting event and not a day of leisure.<n>C: white shoes are often seen in closets.<n>D: white shoes are never meant for the left foot, this is against standard clothing fashion.<n>E: white shoes are, surprisingly, worn in one's home.<n>So the answer is B<n><n>Input: It costs $6.25 to ship 92 pounds of cargo anywhere in the United States.  A large farm sells produce region-wide, and for shipping purposes, pigs weigh no more than 189 pounds.  How much, in dollars and cents, does it cost to ship 57 pigs?<n>Output: For 57 pigs, shipping would cost $217.00.  In other words, it costs $1.15 per 4-ton shipment.<n><n>Input: How much does it cost to feed an elephant?<n>Output: An elephant eats 150 kg of grass each week.<n>Assume 1 week is 7 days; 1 Kg=0.22 lb, 1 kg=2.2 lbs; $0.50 per lb. of feed; $0.55 per 4.4 lbs. (assume 4.4 Kg=9.69 lbs.) <n>Feed a 3-ton elephant 13.3 kg daily; a 5-ton ≈ 19.7 kg daily; $1.057 per 3-ton animal; $1.157 per 5-ton animal.<n>So the cost to feed a elephant for one week =<n>$11.98 for the 3-ton animal and $13.23 for the 5-ton animal<n><n>Input: How many feet is it in a mile?<n>Output: One mile is 5280 feet.<n>1609.34 million people live in the United States. Multiply by 2 (for those over 2, under 2) to make 3218.68 million. Divide by 3 (the children, excluding the 5-
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:What place of work might you find a hairpin? Choices:  A: hair salon B: hair of woman C: barber shop D: pincushion E: woman's hair<n>Output:		The hairpin is at the B option<n>The second option for the question is A. The place where you usually get a hair pin is a hair salon and not a barber shop.<n>The third option for the question is C. Which implies that the hair pin is in the barber shop.<n>To eliminate the option D,<n>The hair pin is made from the hair of a woman and not from a pincushion.<n>Thus, the answer is B<n><n>Input: What kind of job might a person find at a company that sells carpets? Choices:  a. carpet salesperson b. carpet repairer c. carpet collector d. carpet cleaner e. carpet collector<n>Output: The job is in the B option<n>The first option for the question is the salesperson. The position of carpet salesperson requires knowledge of flooring knowledge and does not require a skillset of carpet repair, repairer or cleaner.<n>The second option for question is for a carpet repairer, which is not possible as the person can have knowledge in flooring but will not be able to repair.<n>To eliminate the third and fourth option in the first list of options the last option of collector is eliminated. As the person can collect carpets and flooring is one of the skills a collector will be able to collect.<n>Thus, answer is B<n><n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where is microphone boom likely to be used to record an album? Choices:  A: radio station B: recording studio C: concert D: tv studio E: new york<n>Output:		It will definitely be used in a recordings studio.

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:The old man was retired and liked the simple things, he would do crossword puzzle every morning simply just to do what? He was 10% of the way finished with the contract as measured by "labor performed."  At the daily rate of $10<n>Output: What amount will he have earned for the job?<n>Solution steps:<n>labor performed=10%<n>100000=(10000/10) *10, 10000=1000*10, 1/10*1000=(1/10)*10=10<n><n>1000*9=10000,<n>labor performed=9000/110=<<9000/60=888.8>>88.888888.<n><n>labor performed=88.8, daily rate=10, multiply by 90 will give us $888. Simon would never make a profit off of a cow he takes to a city.<n>Because the cow can only be used for one use.  Simon makes more money off cow when its slaughtered.  There is more incentive to slaughter the cow.  Simon is going to make a $25,000 profit.

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:What could happen after driving car that does not involve pain? Choices:  A: automobile accidents B: backache C: eye strain D: getting tired E: car crash<n>Output:		A<n><n>Input: A person spends $250 each week. How much money does he have after spending $1000?<n>Output: A: The person only have $250<n>B: Not enough = 1000-250=750<n>C: Too Much = 1001-250=<n>D: Too Much =1000+250-750=500<n>E: Too Much =   1000+751=<n><n>Input: There’s a sale on some toys for children. The tank of gas will hold.77 gallons extra for a total of 22.8 +.77 = 23.57 gallons for a total of.77 gallon extra for a total of. A) the range is 388.57 miles.<n>B) Range of tank: 388.87 miles.  Pay for 388 gallons * $2.40 =390.24.
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where will a bullet projectile be found during a war? Choices:  A: battle field B: museum C: weapon D: canon E: tornado<n>Output:		This is based on your personal understanding<n><n>Input: How many miles will a car be driven, if it is driven 15 miles one day, 10 miles the next day, and 25 miles the next day?<n>Output: The total miles will be 15+10+25= <<15+10=20>> 35 miles<n><n>Input:  How many miles will a cashier drive, if he drives 15 miles one way, 10 miles to the other end of town and then 25 miles back?<n>Output: The drive will be 15 miles each way and then 25 back for a total of 15*2+25=22.5 miles<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:A night owl is what you'd head at sunset and you'd hear a what at sunrise? Choices:  A: morning person B: early bird C: lark D: early riser E: rooster<n>Output:		I would head for a night owl as you don't see those in the day light<n>If you saw one at any other time of the day you should get help!<n>A: is an animal that comes out at night.  There are no such birds, therefore there "should be" no such answers.<n>B:  is a person that shows up early in the morning, which again means there "should be" only one option.<n>C:  Larks are a variety of European songbirds, they are early risers.  There are no American songbirds with such a name.<n>Therefore, the only answer should be:<n>No roosters at sunset!  And certainly not at sunrise, or all will hear you scream.......<n><n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where would a Martian find the Indian Ocean? Choices:  A: asia B: southern hemisphere C: planet D: east E: earth<n>Output:		A<n><n>Input: There are two possible destinations for Ally and Ben to take their ski trip. Choices:  A: human B: happy C: dangerous D: strange E: weird<n>Output:		Answer: A.<n><n># Challenge Questions<n><n>### Instruction:Answer the question using an expression of 12 operators and/or functions.<n><n># Challenge A<n><n><n>Input: a = 5<n>b = 2<n>c = 9<n><n>Return (3 a + 5 * b) & div(4 * c, 2)<n>### Instruction Answer Challenge A<n><n><n>### Challenge B<n><n>Input: 20/30 & mul(2, 2) & div(3, 5) & mul(14,4) & sqrt(7)<n>### Instrucion Answer Challenge B<n><n>### Challenge C <n><n>Input: mul(11,2) & div(15,3) & 24% & lcm(11,17) & 5 & sum(sqrt(70%(33))) & sum(10%(6))<n>### Instruction answer Challenge C <n><n># Challenge D<n><n>Input:(sum((12/10)*(21%/16)))+(3/2)+(sqrt(10/5))+(round(25,3))+2*(1/sqrt(6))+(6/(10%))<n><n>Output: 21.0<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where do farmers keep toothpicks? Choices:  A: mouth B: grocery store C: constructing models D: shed E: box<n>Output:		The answer is 'D' - Constructing<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where would you put a dictionary while you're using it? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. B is incorrect because the title of the show does not pertain to what the show is on it pertains to the ranger not being bored by the gardener. <br/><br/<n><n>The show could be about a ranger and a gardener who share the same interests, but the show, which the ranger and the gardener are both on, would not be the countryside because it was a show, not about the countryside. <br/><<n>C would be incorrect because dull read because a dull read would be a book someone is reading that is boring and not exciting. <br/></p><n><br/>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:If I have a vintage, decorative light source in my possession, what is it likely to be? Choices:  A: sun B: sky C: candle D: house E: lamp<n>Output:		The light source is A sun.  I choose A and B as the most probable.<n><n><n>Input: I have a large collection of books, including titles A - S by various authors. I select at random one of two books, U or V. What is the probability that it will be by the same author as a book already selected, X - Y?<n>Output:If I pick U and Y that is 2*2*2=<<2*2*2==6>>6/10 chance that the author for U and Y is the same as they are for X,Y,U,V<n>So the answer is 6/10<n><n>Input:"It feels so good when the sky is blue." According to this sentence, "the sky is" A. something good. B. something sad. C. something true. D. none of the above.<n>Output: "It feels so good when...the sky is blue" means that the sky is something good, as in it feels so good to see the sky<n><n>Input: What is the average temperature in degrees on a cool day in Houston, TX? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:He was good at traditional science but excelled at social science, his favorite subject was what? Choices:  A: geography B: history studies C: math D: religion E: dancing<n>Output:		His favorite subject was geography because he was good at both traditional and social science.<n>Since history was listed, math and religion were eliminated<n>A car travels at a rate of 55 miles per hour in a straight line for 150 minutes.  How far did it travel?<n>Output: If the car is going 55 mph at 150 minutes, it travels 6 miles.<n><n>Input:  A person in an automobile accelerates at a rate of 26 feet per second per second for 50 seconds until it has a speed of 85 miles per hour.  How far does the car travel, in miles?<n>Output: The car travels <<85*26=2220>>2220 feets in 0.5 * 26 = 130 mins<n>Total = 1300000/1000 = 130 miles<n>Final answer is 130<n><n>Input: The time interval between 12:30 A. M and 6:00 P. M last Tuesday was<n><n>1.  2 hours and 30 minutes<n><n>2.  2 hours and  30 minutes<n><n>3.  3 hours and  20 minutes<n><n>Output: Time period which is 2 hour and 30 minute is right one<n><n>Input: The length of a bus route in Manhattan is approximately 40 miles long.  How long can a bus run nonstop from the east side of the Upper East Side to the Lower East Side and back?  <n><n>Output: <<40 * (1 + 40/60)>>40*((1+(40/60)))<n><n>50 minutes<n><n>Input: The distance between two cities, in miles, is equal to 1,000 miles less 1/5th the difference between the speed of light and their speed limit.  What is the 1/8th of this difference, in miles?<n><n>Output: Useful information:<n><n>Speed of light = 186,282 miles per second<n><n>Based on speed limits stated:<n><n>100 mph => <186,272 / 4 >= 100>=> 46 mph<n><n>55 mph
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:If you have trouble beginning work you're suffering from what? Choices:  A: sitting down B: excitement C: tiredness D: progress E: procrastination<n>Output:		Procrastination<n>I feel sick. I haven't eaten for 10 days<n><n>-[Procrastination on MSDN wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Procrastination)<n><n>### Instruction:Enter code to solve the problem<n><n>#### Instruction:Write to stdout the sum of the even numbers from 100 to 200<n><n>#### Instruction:`for n in {100..200}`<n><n>```python<n>>>> n=71<n>```<n><n>```python<n>n=71<n>>>> print('n=%s' % hex(n), n)<n>n=71 0x71<n>```<n>### Instruction:`sum = 0`<n>```python<n>>>x=1<n>while x <= 99:`<n>    sum+=(x>>1) & 1<n>    x += 1<n>`<n>>>p=x<n>>>n=p % 17<n>>>sum+=(n>>1) & 4<n>>>print(sum)`<n>61<n>```<n>

Solve each part separately:<n><n>income=(20%)(500)(10000)/1000000;  income=(20% of 500)($10000/$10000))<n><n>subtract the units purchased;<n>Subtract income=20%*500*(10000-500)*(10000+500)/10;<n>Subtract(1000-5) =20%*5*120/10;<n><n>income=(15%)(n)r<n>Subtract income =500-(15% of 5)*(5*100)/10<n>Subtract income (55)*(5*5)/(55)<n><n>income = (15%*(55*495)/55<n><n>Add units sold and profit<n><n>= 15% (6480/7)*$100 * 40 to get a rounded $15,200<n><n><n>Input: A person has a new house with a large front flower bed. The code with 0 left and no 2s right is 0300.  The code with no 0s is 4308 The code with no 2s is 438.  How many 3's are in the code to the locker?<n>Output:6. Three times two is six, therefore 1 (one) three is six. But since 8 = 6 + 2, there were two threes. So the answer is seven
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:You can read a magazine where while waiting for your transportation on rails to arrive? Choices:  A: train station B: bookstore C: newsstand D: waiting room E: airport<n>Output:		Answer:E; the most common places to wait for transportation or a flight are airport(s) and train stations (E & D), both of which have a train-track themed waiting area. However, news-stands and book-stores have never offered train or plane travel related articles because you need to be there personally to read the information.<n><n>Input:How many minutes are there in 3 hours?<n>Output:Answer:180 minutes; since 3 does not end in zero the correct answer is 180. However, it may seem reasonable to put a zero in front of each three to count 60,90, and 100 minutes which would sum to 240 minutes instead of 180. If you don't believe in doing maths, then put an E, S, or T after each three-letter word in this sentence and then count them; for example: One hundred eighty-zero minutes = (3*20)+(60*4)+(100*5) => 3*20+240+5*100=230+360+500=1190<n><n>Input:A baseball team is using a $40,000.00 check to pay the owner of a new stadium in a small town.<n>Therefore the team must earn at least $40,072.00 in the next 4 seasons to cover the costs.  However, the owner doesn’t want the team to lose because of the $40,028.00 they need to make above expenses. How many wins for each of the next 4 seasons would it take to break even, if there are at least 31 games in each season?<n>Output:Answer A 27 win season: Let X=# of wins in a single season.<n>40,070=4X+[(1-0.03)(4-x)]+[(0.07*86-0.07*40-0.07)X+4+0.07274-0.03-((0.274)(2X*(1-0.07*(86-x))))((1-0.0274)(X-0.0
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:The policemen wanted to clear the scene of the accident, so what did they do to traffic? Choices:  A: hurry along B: direct traffic C: help D: force open door E: corner thief<n>Output:		A, Hurry Along<n><n>Input:When does the new quarter start? A: green left arrow B: green right arrow C: orange right arrow D: red light E: green left arrow<n>Output: B: Green Arrow<n><n>Input: When should you not use your mobile phone while driving a car? He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:When a newborn's eyes open for the first time it will be the first time the ever? Choices:  A: tear up B: see light C: fill with tears D: be happy E: glass over<n>Output:		Choice D Eye opening is in regards to the baby's eye<n>As the child's eye opens and they see everything around them for the first time they will be very happy or they will be scared for the majority of young children..<n>So the final answer will be D or E<n><n>Input: You can take the train from Twin Falls, ID to Yellowstone National Park in Bozeman, MT every 2 hours and it costs $30/ride. You are planning 2 trips per day, but you will need to have a place to stay in Yellowstone Park so your total expense will be $300/day.<n>How much will you spend for 3 days?<n>Output: The train every 2hrs = 6 trips each day, if you were staying a total of 3days then that would be 21 trips<n>The trips cost $30 = $900<n>The total cost of a place to stay is $300/Day=$1100/21days = $53.81 per trip<n>Therefore, the total cost will $1100+30= $1130<n><n>Input: You are at the bookstore trying to find the perfect book for your son’s birthday. You notice that there is a “3 for $20” sale. You are considering getting your son a biography on Winston Churchill (price $12), a biography on Nelson Mandela (price $14), and a history book on Alexander the Great (price $18). How much money would you spend if you picked that third book?<n>Output: The “3 for $2o” sale requires that you buy a minimum of three books and in this case we require three books for sure, so we can buy 3 books for $20 = 60$<n>The price of the first book is 12$, the second book is 14$ and the last is 18$<n>If we purchase the 3 books for $60 the last book will cost 20-60=-$40<n><n>Input : Choose the true sentence. Choices:<n>A: The sum of the 1st and 2nd numbers is 3 times the sum of the 2nd and the 3rd numbers.<n>B:
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where do people find bills with bread? Choices:  A: restaurant B: congress C: envelope D: mail box E: cheese store<n>Output:		The correct answer is [D-Envelope](Cod-blocks:0)<n><n>Input:What’s the solution to 1+1+1+1=<<1+1+1…>+15>+1? Choose 1 or 2<n>Output:  The solution is either a) or b) <n>It is not 12 or 13. So the answer is 14.<n><n><n>Input: A rectangular box is 2 feet by 3 feet.  What is the area of the box?<n>Output: Area of the box = 2 * 3 = 6<n>So, the answer is 6 sq. ft<n><n>Input: What is 4/3 times 5 +?<n>Output: (4/3) (5 +?) = (12/3)*5+(14?/3) = 10 12 2/3<n>So, the answer (4/3)^(5+?) = (4/3)^12 = 12<n><n>Input: What times 30 is equal to -10?<n><n>Output: (3/5)*10=3/5*-10=-5/5=-1<n>So, the answer to this question is -5<n><n>Input: What does 2 divided by 0 return?<n><n>Output: 2/0 = infinity<n><n>Input: What are two prime factors of the number 30?<n><n>Output:-Two prime factors of the number are 5X5/2=5/1=5<n><n>Input: Which of the following is not a square number?<n><n>Output:-1 is not a square number as it is not a perfect square<n><n>Input: What can make 100?<n><n>Output:-2*2*2*2<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Where can you eat fruit on a red bridge? Choices:  A: refrigerator B: engineering school C: san francisco D: tree E: market<n>Output:		F(red) = refrigerator G(red) = tree H(red) = f(2010) = san francisco  f = refrigerator <n>A(red) = re<n>A(2010)= engineering school <n>E(red) = re in 2010 <n>F(2010 + 2003) = market<n><n> <n>'''<n><n>F(red) = re frigerator<n><n><n>#Solution:<n>def test_one_string(input_str):<n>    answer=[]<n>    counter=1<n>    if len(input_str)==0:<n>        return answer['error']<n>    elif input_str[-1]==':':<n>        return  answer['error']<n><n>    for i in range(1,len(input_str)):<n>        if input_str[i]==input_str[-1]:<n>            counter+=1<n>        else:<n>            if counter==1:<n>                counter=1<n>                answer.append(i)<n>            if counter==4:<n>                counter=4<n>                answer.append(-1)<n><n>    if counter in 5..5:<n>        answer.append(<n>            'The first 7 days were '+str(int(input_str[0:counter])-<n>         input_str[0:4]))<n>        answer.append('The additional 4 days' +' were :'+ str(int(input_st[counter+1:]))<n> <n>        input_str=[i for i in input_str if -2**32 < (i-input_str[0])<2**32 if 'i' == i.title().replace('I','')]<n><n>        input_str.sort()<n>        for i in range(0,len(input_st)):<n>            if input_str[1+i]==0:<n>                answer.append('190')<n><n>            answer.append(input_str[1+<n>                               i])<n>            #answer.append(str((int(input_st)+10-input_st[1+<n>            #         i])/4))<n>            answer.append(' was '+<n>                str(input_st[1+(i+1):]))<n>    else:
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:What makes people happy when it is surprising and unexpected? Choices:  A: joke B: humor C: frightened D: fight E: laughter<n>Output:		The correct answer is choice B<n>Input: The word for this lesson in Spanish is …… Choices:  A. la clase de hoy  B. hoy  C. hoy estamos hablando  D. La clase de hoy es este tiempo  E. el hoy de la clase<n>Output: The correct word for the lesson in Spanish is Choice A.<n><n>Input: There are 180 students in Mr. Johnson’s history class. He hands out 25 quizzes and collects them later in the day. He gives 30 points to each student who passes the quiz and deducts 10 points for each incorrect answer. If a student fails to submit a quiz, that student is given a zero. How many students passed the quiz?<n>Output: To determine the pass-fail breakdown, set up the table shown:Passed______________ ______________ Failed.<n>The number of students passed = 85 because 85+85+30+0 = <85+85-10+0=160>160.<n>The number of failed students = 95 because 160-85 = <160-80=80>80.<n>So, the number of students who passed the test = 85<85> and the number of failed students =95<95>.<n><n><n>Input: A shoe store offers a 40% discount if you buy two pair of shoes. The shop’s price is $70 with a minimum of 14 shoes for sale, and a max of 26. A student who bought at this store has told you they bought three pair of shoes for $74. For me, 8 two’s is the smallest, so I’ll use eight (8).<n>40% of 70 $28<n>65% of 70$
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out.  He’s charging $50.00 per day or $500.00 for 14 days.  Eric wants to rent the house for 20 days.  How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:The man took 3 hours every morning for grooming, what is the likely result with his job? Choices:  A: tardiness B: looking good C: injury D: vacation E: neatness<n>Output:		Tardiness<n>The man takes 3 hours for grooming, so then the man takes 21 hours for everything else he does (17 hours for job and 4 hours for leisure)<n>So then 22*60 = <<22*60=1320>>1320 minutes and 22*6+((3-17)/6*24) = <<58-7==0>>0 minutes<n>The result of the problem is 1320+58+7= <<1320+0+586>>1320+8+58586>>58586 total minutes, so 24 hours and 58 minutes.
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: The car-rental agency charges $30/day for a car, or $190 for the first week for a rental that lasts an entire week or longer. Jennie rented a car for 11 days. How much, in dollars, did she pay for the rental?<n>Output: The first 7 days were $190.<n>There were 11-7=<<11-7=4>>4 days left.<n>The additional 4 days were 4*30=<<4*30=120>>120.<n>And 190+120=<<190+120=310>>310.<n>So the final answer is 310<n><n>Input: A hurricane is approaching the southern coast of Texas, and a rancher is planning to move 400 head of cattle 60 miles to higher ground to protect them from possible inland flooding that might occur.  His animal transport truck holds 20 head of cattle.  Traveling at 60 miles per hour, what is the total driving time, in hours, it will take to transport all of his cattle to higher ground?<n>Output: Given the limited capacity of his transport vehicle (20 head of cattle), the 400 head of cattle will require 400/20=<<400/20=20>>20 trips using his transport vehicle.<n>Traveling to the site at 60 mph for 60 miles it will take 60/60=<<60/60=1>>1 hour to travel one-way.<n>Since each trip requires driving to and returning from the relocation site, each complete round trip will take 2*1=<<2*1=2>>2 hours.<n>Thus, 20 complete trips will take 20*2=<<20*2=40>>40 hours of driving time.<n>So the final answer is 40<n><n>Input: Jason has a carriage house that he rents out. How much will it cost him?<n>Output: He wants to rent for 20 days and there is a deal if you rent for 14 days so that leaves 20-14 = <<20-14=6>>6 individual days<n>Each individual day is $50.00 and he will have 6 individual days for a total of 50*6 = $<<50*6=300.00>>300.00<n>14 days costs $500.00 and 6 days costs $300.00 for a total of 500+300 = $800.00<n>So the final answer is 800<n><n>Input:Dancing for a long time will lead you to become what? Choices:  A: sore B: intercourse C: fatigue D: become tired E: expression<n>Output:		A<n><n>#### Solution:<n><n>1. Input: <n>The car-rental agen...<n>```<n>$ 190 (7)<n>$190 (7)? (11?4) - $190 == $310<n>$310 (4) 1950 <n>$190 * 11 - $190 * 7 <n>$310<n>```<n>*Note:<n>1) the total cost for the first 7 days is $190 because in total it is 7 days<n>2) remaining 11-7 = 4 days = 4 trips of transfering.<n>3) 4 x $30 = $120<n>4) 190 +120 =<n>5) 970<n>6) 310<n>![Instution](https://i.gllearn.cn/2020-07-23%20instruction.png)<n>---<n><a href="https://github.com/GLProgramming/GLProgramming">GLProgramming</a><n>2016-2021.
